Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Garlic Cloves{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Put the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} and garlic parcel onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halfway through cooking, remove the garlic parcel and turn the sausages.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, in a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams} and @Mayonnaise{32%grams}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your slaw aside.

A few mins before the chips and sausages are ready, slice the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through).

Slide them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}. Mix it into the slaw.

When everything's ready, transfer the buns to your plates. Fill the buns with the sausages.

Drizzle over the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams} and the @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}, then sprinkle on the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Serve the chips and slaw alongside.

Enjoy!